<TITLE> KUET closed after clash leaves25 hurt </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 4 (bdnews24.com)The Khulna University of Engineering and Technology was shut Monday until May 30 after two groups of students clashed on the campus over a cultural function on Sunday night, leaving 25 people injured. The authorities asks the students to vacate all five residential halls by 8pm. Among those injured were 19 students, three journalists and as many policemen. Two of the injured students who could not be immediately named were admitted to Khulna Medical College Hospital. The injured journalists are senior staff reporter Kanak Rahman of The Daily Samakal, staff reporter Rana Kabir of Dainik Purbanchal and cameraman of Channel 1 Haider Ali. The students beat them up in a classroom before police rescued them. Witnesses said police hurled charged teargas to quell the violence that erupted at around 11am and continued through to 5pm. Both groups armed with brickbats, sticks, hockey sticks and iron rods vandalised several rooms of the halls. Police cordoned the university and the residential halls as tension ran high as students continued to protest against the order to leave halls and close the university. bdnews2
